<!-- research -->
<p>
    Throughout the project, I had reoccuring interviews with 5 intermediate-advanced weight lifters. In the initial 
    phase I had them all answer a google survey I put together. I made conclusions on primary motivations, important 
    values, and adding specific features, like an AI chatbot. The data from the discussions allowed me to create a 
    user persona, journey maps, compare competitors in the current market. 
</p>
<!-- process -->
<p>
    This was an independent project. Design sprint 1 was for research while the rest was focused on increasing the 
    fidelity of the prototypes. My approach to design was very top-down—having decided on specific features and 
    figuring out how to add it. My specific process looked like analyzing competitors features or bits of software 
    that have served me in the past and creating my own variation of it. I used sites like Dribble and explored 
    many different products (not just fitness ones) to inspire my design. 
</p>
